Readme v 1

The Cyclistic case study, using online bike sharing datasets, was an option for the end-of-course Capstone in the Google Data Analytics Course at Coursera. Curiosity about how AI vibe coding compares to the technical skills from this course led me to run the case study through Claude for comparison.

Claude delivered a thorough, professional deck and annotated notebook on almost its first try. On a first read, it all looks plausible and the insights are what one would expect, like casual riders spiking in warmer months.  
https://www.coursera.org/professional-certificates/google-data-analytics 
